    "Only after the action cards are solid should you let the AI summarize or ground on longer reference text."
  ],
  "handoffNotes": {
    "bestApproach": "Give Replit a structured package, not one giant vague prompt.",
    "stages": [
      "Stage 1: models and seed data (Guide, ActionCard, SourceReference, risk metadata).",
      "Stage 2: guide browsing UI and action-card UI.",
      "Stage 3: retrieval policy and response templates.",
      "Stage 4: AI grounding on top of the finished guides."
    ],
    "documentRole": "Use this content pack as a stable source file you can upload to Replit and keep revising."
  }
